<span id="iv.x.xlii-p1"></span> <span class="c2"><span
id="iv.x.xlii-p1.1"></span>Chapter 40.—Neither Can God Suffer Hurt, Nor
Any Other, Save by the Just Ordination of God.</span>

<span id="iv.x.xlii-p2"></span>Since these things are so, according to
the Catholic faith, and wholesome doctrine, and truth perspicuous to
those of good understanding, neither can any one hurt the nature of God,
nor can the nature of God unrighteously hurt any one, or suffer any one
to do hurt with impunity.  "For he that doeth hurt shall receive," says
the apostle, "according to the hurt that he has done; and there is no
accepting of persons with God." <span
id="fr_1133"></span>[1134](#fn_1133.md)

